# Stripe Payment Integration Project

## Description

This project demonstrates how to integrate Stripe payments in a web application. It uses Node.js along with environment variables to securely handle your Stripe secret key. You can run the development server and test the checkout functionality using the `checkout.html` file.

## Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone the Repository

First, clone the repository and navigate into the project directory:

### 2. Set ENV File (.env)

Create .env file in root directory

STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test\*\*\*\*

### 3. Install Dependency and Run

```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```

### 4. Open the Checkout Page

You can access and test the checkout functionality by either:
Opening the checkout.html file directly in your browser, or Using the Live Server extension in your code editor (like Visual Studio Code) to serve the file and view it in the browser.
